  <dialog class="os-request-modal" data-request-modal aria-labelledby="request-title"><form method="dialog" class="os-modal-card" data-request-form><button class="os-modal-close" value="cancel" aria-label="Close request panel">×</button><p class="os-eyebrow">COMING NEXT</p><h2 id="request-title" data-request-title>Employment Contracts</h2><p>This Decision Episode is still being developed. Your question helps determine what BOMSociety builds next.</p><label for="request-question">What would you most want help deciding?</label><p class="os-modal-hint">One useful question is enough. Optional context stays out of standard analytics.</p><textarea id="request-question" name="question" rows="3" maxlength="600" placeholder="Optional — do not include identifying details."></textarea><button type="submit" class="os-button">Submit my question <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button><p class="os-request-confirmation" data-request-confirmation hidden aria-live="polite"></p></form></dialog>
  <section class="os-episode" id="compensation-pathway" hidden aria-labelledby="episode-title"><div class="shell">
    <div class="os-episode-label"><div><p class="os-eyebrow">FLAGSHIP DECISION EPISODE</p><h2 id="episode-title">Compensation, made legible.</h2></div><p>Move at the depth you need. Your progress stays private in this browser.</p></div>
    <ol class="os-steps" aria-label="Decision Episode steps"><li class="is-active" data-step="problem">Problem</li><li data-step="context">Context</li><li data-step="big">Big Picture</li><li data-step="brief">Brief Overview</li><li data-step="deep">Deep Dive</li><li data-step="calculator">Calculator</li><li data-step="checklist">Checklist</li><li data-step="action">Action Plan</li><li data-step="reflection">Reflection</li><li data-step="outcome">OUTCOME</li><li data-step="share">SHARE</li></ol>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="problem"><p class="os-eyebrow">PROBLEM</p><h2>What part of this compensation decision is unclear?</h2><p>Separate the headline number from the formula, terms, and evidence you need before you decide.</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="context">Set the context <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="context" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">CONTEXT</p><h2>Use the offer and the work behind it.</h2><p>Keep the written offer, expected workload, attribution rules, and reconciliation schedule in view. They determine whether the number fits your situation.</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="big">See the Big Picture <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="big" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">BIG PICTURE · 30 SECONDS</p><h2>A compensation number is not a compensation formula.</h2><div class="os-formula"><b>YOUR COMPENSATION</b><span>Guarantee</span><i>+</i><span>Productivity</span><i>+</i><span>Quality</span><i>+</i><span>Call / leadership</span><i>−</i><span>Unseen conditions</span></div><div class="os-insights"><p><b>01</b> The headline salary may only be the guarantee.</p><p><b>02</b> Thresholds and attribution determine what work pays.</p><p><b>03</b> Reconciliation tells you whether the formula works in practice.</p></div><div class="os-stat"><strong>One request can change the entire conversation.</strong><span>Ask for the full written formula and two recent reconciliation statements.</span></div><p class="os-transition">You understand the formula. Next, test the offer.</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="brief">Continue to Brief Overview <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="brief" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">BRIEF OVERVIEW · 2 MINUTES</p><h2>Same salary. Different economics.</h2><div class="os-offers"><div><span>OFFER A</span><b>$300k</b><p>Clear threshold · Quarterly reconciliation · Defined attribution</p></div><div><span>OFFER B</span><b>$300k</b><p>High threshold · Annual reconciliation · Unclear exclusions</p></div></div><p class="os-transition">You can now identify the terms that change compensation.</p><p class="os-action"><strong>Three questions to bring:</strong> What is the threshold? What is the conversion factor? What work is credited to me?</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="deep">Work through the Deep Dive <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="deep" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">DEEP DIVE · 5 MINUTES</p><h2>Turn a number into questions you can use.</h2><div class="os-deep"><div><h3>Before the conversation</h3><ol><li>Request the written formula and definitions.</li><li>Identify the threshold and conversion factor.</li><li>Clarify attribution, quality, call, and payment timing.</li><li>Ask how disagreements are resolved.</li></ol></div><div><h3>Common blind spots</h3><ul><li>Assuming the guarantee is the whole deal.</li><li>Missing work excluded from attribution.</li><li>Accepting undefined quality adjustments.</li><li>Waiting a year for reconciliation.</li></ul></div></div><p class="os-transition">You now have the framework. Turn it into action.</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="calculator">Build my next-step checklist <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="calculator" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">INTERACTIVE CALCULATOR</p><h2>Make the formula visible.</h2><div class="os-calculator"><label>Guaranteed compensation <input data-calc="guarantee" type="number" value="300000" min="0"></label><label>Credited wRVUs <input data-calc="units" type="number" value="6000" min="0"></label><label>Threshold wRVUs <input data-calc="threshold" type="number" value="5000" min="0"></label><label>Conversion factor <input data-calc="factor" type="number" value="55" min="0"></label><output data-calculator-result>Illustrative total: $355,000</output><small>Educational illustration only; actual terms and payment rules vary.</small></div><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="checklist">Save your checklist <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="checklist" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">CHECKLIST</p><h2>Leave with a clear request.</h2><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Request the complete written compensation formula.</label><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Ask for two recent reconciliation statements.</label><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Confirm attribution, quality, and dispute terms.</label><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="action">Build my action plan <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="action" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">ACTION PLAN</p><h2>Your next conversation, prepared.</h2><p class="os-quote">“Please provide the productivity formula, threshold, conversion factor, attribution rules, quality measures, and reconciliation schedule in writing.”</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="reflection">Record your confidence <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="reflection" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">REFLECTION</p><h2>What changed in your understanding?</h2><p>Save a private confidence check. It is stored only in this browser.</p><div class="os-confidence" data-confidence-options aria-label="Confidence from zero to ten"></div><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="outcome">See your Decision Win <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="outcome" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">YOUR DECISION WIN</p><h2>You now know exactly what compensation formula to request.</h2><div class="os-decision-win"><span>✓</span><p>Estimated impact: <strong>potentially material value over the life of this agreement.</strong><br><small>That is a possibility—not a promise. The next step is a better question.</small></p></div><div class="os-outcome-capture"><p><strong>Did this help?</strong> Stored only as an anonymized, consented response.</p><button type="button" data-outcome="helpful">Yes, it helped</button><button type="button" data-outcome="revisit">I will revisit after my meeting</button></div><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="share">Help a colleague <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="share" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">KNOW · DO · SHARE</p><h2>Finish with a better Business of Medicine decision.</h2><div class="os-next-actions"><p><strong>KNOW</strong><br>You learned that a compensation number is not a compensation formula.</p><p><strong>DO</strong><br>Ask for the complete written compensation formula before evaluating the offer.</p><p><strong>SHARE</strong><br>Send this framework to a colleague reviewing an offer.</p></div><div class="os-next-actions"><button type="button" class="os-text-link" data-save-action>Save this action</button><button type="button" class="os-text-link" data-share>Send to a colleague</button><button type="button" class="os-text-link" data-reflection>Record what I plan to do</button><a class="os-text-link" href="#compensation-pathway">Return after the conversation</a></div><div class="os-share-context"><h3>Know someone reviewing an offer?</h3><p>Send them the compensation framework before their next conversation.</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-share>Send to a colleague <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></div></article>
  </div></section>


  <section class="os-enterprise" aria-labelledby="enterprise-title"><div class="shell os-enterprise-grid"><div><p class="os-eyebrow">BUSINESS OF MEDICINE INTELLIGENCE</p><h2 id="enterprise-title">Every anonymous Decision Episode helps improve Business of Medicine guidance while protecting the physician.</h2><p>Physicians remain free. individual physician data is never sold. Enterprise revenue funds better physician guidance.</p><div class="os-trust-list"><span>Anonymous by design</span><span>Aggregated before insight</span><span>Transparent about what is next</span></div></div><div class="os-enterprise-actions"><p><strong>Built physician-first.</strong> Future intelligence is in development, with governance before commercial use.</p><a class="os-button" href="{{@site.url}}/enterprise/">Explore the Business of Medicine Intelligence platform <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a><a class="os-text-link" href="{{@site.url}}/privacy/">See how privacy works <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></div></div></section>
</main>
